  "title": "Food Production Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Core Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p>• \tProduction Operations</p><p>• \tOperate and monitor food processing equipment and machinery.</p><p>• \tAssist in preparing, mixing, cooking, and packaging food products according to recipes and specifications.</p><p>• \tEnsure production targets are met efficiently and on time.</p><p>• \tQuality Assurance</p><p>• \tConduct routine checks to maintain product quality and consistency.</p><p>• \tFollow strict hygiene, safety, and sanitation standards in all production areas.</p><p>• \tReport and resolve any deviations or defects in raw materials or finished products.</p><p>• \tCompliance & Safety</p><p>• \tAdhere to food safety regulations (e.g., HACCP, GMP).</p><p>• \tMaintain accurate records of production processes, batch numbers, and quality checks.</p><p>• \tSupport audits and inspections by regulatory bodies.</p><p>• \tMaintenance & Troubleshooting</p><p>• \tPerform basic maintenance and cleaning of equipment.</p><p>• \tIdentify and report mechanical or process issues to supervisors.</p><p>• \tAssist in implementing corrective actions to minimize downtime.</p><p>• \tCollaboration</p><p>• \tWork closely with production supervisors, quality control teams, and warehouse staff.</p><p>• \tSupport training of new staff on equipment use and safety protocols.</p><p>• \tCommunicate effectively to ensure smooth workflow across departments.</p><p><u><strong>Key Skills & Competencies</strong></u></p><p>• \tKnowledge of food processing techniques and equipment</p><p>• \tStrong attention to detail and commitment to hygiene standards</p><p>• \tAbility to follow instructions and standard operating procedures (SOPs)</p><p>• \tBasic mechanical aptitude for handling production machinery</p><p>• \tTeamwork and communication skills</p><p>• \tPhysical stamina to handle long shifts and repetitive tasks<br /></p><p><u><strong>Work Hour: </strong></u><br />•     Monday - Sunday : 5 am - 3 pm<br />•     Must work on Sunday and Public Holiday, a day off in lieu on a weekday will be given. </p>",
